comments: Westbrook (LAL) moves into Hunter's (ATL) path on the drive but the contact is marginal.
Monk (LAL) reaches in and makes contact to the arm of Hunter (ATL) after that gather that impacts his driving shot attempt at the rim.
Bogdanovic (ATL) and Westbrook (LAL) compete for the rebound off of the free throw and Bogdanovic is the last to touch the ball before it bounces out of bounds.
Johnson (LAL) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Bogdanovic (ATL) and incidental contact occurs during the screening action.
Hunter (ATL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bradley (LAL) and incidental contact occurs as the defensive players switch the screen.
Bogdanovic (ATL) reaches in and his fingertips graze the right arm of Westbrook (LAL) during the latter's drive. The marginal contact does not impact Westbrook's subsequent pass out of the drive.

Davis (LAL) establishes himself in a wide screening position in the path of Hunter (ATL) and some marginal contact occurs. However, Hunter's momentum was taking him in the opposite direction of Westbrook and the marginal contact from the screen did not impact Hunter's ability to play defense.
Hunter (ATL) wraps his arm around Davis's (LAL) right shoulder and affects his ability to get to the rebound.
Bradley (LAL) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
Hunter (ATL) legally contests the shot attempt in the paint from Westbrook (LAL).
Reaves (LAL) commits a take foul on Bogdanovic (ATL).
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Huerter (ATL) and absorbs the contact on the screen as the defensive player trails his offensive matchup.
Huerter (ATL) legally contests Monk (LAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
